     5	
     6	# Harnessloop Status
     7	
     8	Read Harnessloop state safely. This skill reports current loop state; it must not create files, update contracts, archive handoffs, run business execution, or continue the task.
     9	
    10	## Input Contract
    11	
    12	Accept an explicit skill invocation such as `$harnessloop-status`, or natural language asking for current Harnessloop state. Treat `harnessloop:status` and `harnessloop status` as natural-language aliases only; `$harnessloop:status` is not a valid skill invocation.
    13	
    14	Useful input includes:
    15	
    16	- `target-project`: defaults to the current working directory.
    17	- Optional state path, usually `.harnessloop/state/current.md`.
    18	- Optional scope: active goal, active round, evidence, handoffs, control, environment, self-audit, or next action.
    19	
    20	If `.harnessloop/` is missing, report `not-initialized` and suggest `$harnessloop-init`. Do not initialize it from this skill.
    21	
    22	If `.harnessloop/` exists but `check_setup.py` reports `complete: false`, report `setup-incomplete`, surface `field_todo_count` and `selfcheck_todo_count` and every non-`filled` file's `missing_sections`, and suggest `$harnessloop-setup`. Do not run the wizard from this skill.
    23	
    24	## Processing Contract
    25	
    26	1. Read `.harnessloop/state/current.md` first when present.
    27	2. Run `python3 -B <plugin-root>/skills/harnessloop-loop/scripts/check_setup.py --project <target-project> --json` (the `-B` flag, or `PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1`, guarantees no `__pycache__` bytecode is written, keeping this step strictly read-only). If it reports `complete: false`, set state to `setup-incomplete` and record `field_todo_count` and `selfcheck_todo_count`, the first non-`filled` file, and its `missing_sections` as the setup completeness and next setup step. Note whether `gate_blocking` is `true` (a core policy file — environment/control-contract/cost-context-policy — is still `template`/`missing`) or `false` (only non-blocking gaps, such as `data-sources.md` or `self-check.md`, remain); report this distinction so the user knows whether `$harnessloop-continue` will short-circuit.
